isoiec80000:term-t11-8.21-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Ampère number"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:fullForm .

isoiec80000:sym-t11-8.21-0 a smart:Term, skosxl:Label ;
  skosxl:literalForm "Am"@en ;
  smart:hasTermFormType smart:symbol .

isoiec80000:t11-8.21 a isoiec80000:Quantity, smart:TermEntry ;
  dcterms:identifier "11-8.21" ;
  skosxl:prefLabel isoiec80000:term-t11-8.21-0 ;
  skosxl:altLabel isoiec80000:sym-t11-8.21-0 ;
  skos:definition """relation between electric surface current and magnetic field strength in an electrically conducting liquid, expressed by

stem:[Am = I_A // lH]; where

stem:[I_A]:: is electric surface current,
stem:[l]:: is characteristic length (<<iso80000-3>>), and
stem:[H]:: is magnetic field strength (<<iec80000-6>>)
"""@en ;
  skos:note """This number is also called ((magnetic field number)).

The electric surface current is given by

stem:[I_A = rho_A I mu E]; where

stem:[rho_A]:: is surface density of electric charge (<<iec80000-6>>),
stem:[l]:: is characteristic length (<<iso80000-3>>),
stem:[mu]:: is mobility (<<iso80000-10>>) of charge carriers, and
stem:[E]:: is electric field strength (<<iec80000-6>>).
"""@en ;
  smart:hasBindingnessType smart:normative ;
  dcterms:isPartOf isoiec80000:part-11-8 .